RICK: Can you just confirm
that you're the ad agency

15:00.274 --> 15:02.902
that made the I Got My Life
Back promotional video?

15:02.902 --> 15:04.320
AD EXEC: Yes, that was ours.

15:04.320 --> 15:06.030
RANDY: After reviewing it,
we were curious

15:06.030 --> 15:10.284
as to why nobody says
"OxyContin"

15:10.284 --> 15:14.122
in a video designed
to promote OxyContin.

15:14.122 --> 15:15.790
‐ They don't?
RICK: No.

15:15.790 --> 15:17.917
There's maybe one mention,
40 minutes.

15:17.917 --> 15:19.961
Everyone just says either, uh,

15:19.961 --> 15:23.339
"the pain medication"
or "the pain medicine."

15:23.339 --> 15:25.299
‐ You got people
tying themselves up

15:25.299 --> 15:26.884
not to say OxyContin.

15:26.884 --> 15:29.137
Now, why is that?

15:29.137 --> 15:31.431
‐ I don't remember,
and that shoot was years ago.

15:31.431 --> 15:32.515
‐ Uh‐huh.

15:32.515 --> 15:33.975
‐ And it's important
our clients know

15:33.975 --> 15:35.601
we won't disclose
internal communication.

15:35.601 --> 15:37.019
‐ And it's important
that you know

15:37.019 --> 15:38.646
that we have subpoena power.

15:38.646 --> 15:40.440
So you can either
answer our questions here,

15:40.440 --> 15:41.774
or you can answer 'em
under oath

15:41.774 --> 15:44.110
in front of a grand jury
in Roanoke, Virginia.

15:44.110 --> 15:46.737
‐ Which is beautiful
this time of year.

15:46.737 --> 15:50.741
You see, guys, right now,
we view y'all as witnesses,

15:50.741 --> 15:52.910
but that can quickly change
to suspects.

15:57.623 --> 16:00.334
‐ Look, this was all
a long time ago, okay?

16:00.334 --> 16:01.878
But we might've been
given instructions

16:01.878 --> 16:03.421
that they didn't want
the participants

16:03.421 --> 16:05.214
to say the name
of the medication.

16:05.214 --> 16:06.466
‐ Why not?

16:07.967 --> 16:10.928
‐ If I recall,
the original concept

16:10.928 --> 16:13.389
wasn't to promote OxyContin.

16:13.389 --> 16:15.558
They just wanted us to do
a public service announcement

16:15.558 --> 16:17.268
for pain relief.

16:17.268 --> 16:19.437
‐ That might've been why
Purdue didn't want anyone

16:19.437 --> 16:20.855
to name a specific drug.

16:20.855 --> 16:23.274
‐ But there are titles
at the end

16:23.274 --> 16:25.443
that say OxyContin.

16:25.443 --> 16:27.361
And it's written
at the bottom of the screen

16:27.361 --> 16:29.739
the exact milligrams
each patient's on.

16:29.739 --> 16:33.451
‐ You need to clarify
this issue.

16:33.451 --> 16:36.037
‐ We were given instructions
to add the OxyContin graphics

16:36.037 --> 16:38.456
after the shoot while
we were editing the video.

16:38.456 --> 16:41.459
‐ So it started out as a PSA,

16:41.459 --> 16:43.503
and then somewhere
in the post‐production process,

16:43.503 --> 16:45.338
it became a promotional video
for OxyContin?

16:45.338 --> 16:46.506
Is that what happened?

16:46.506 --> 16:48.216
AD EXEC:
We just did what they wanted.

16:48.216 --> 16:50.801
They said, "Make a PSA,"
so that's what we shot.

16:50.801 --> 16:54.388
Then in post, they said
"Add the OxyContin titles,"

16:54.388 --> 16:55.806
so we did.

16:55.806 --> 16:56.974
‐ So who at Purdue Pharma

16:56.974 --> 16:59.810
gave you
these specific instructions?

16:59.810 --> 17:02.021
♪ ♪

17:02.021 --> 17:03.397
BROWNLEE: Oh, let me guess.

17:03.397 --> 17:05.566
They had no names of any
upper‐level Purdue executives

17:05.566 --> 17:07.485
tied to the video.
‐ No, sir.

17:07.485 --> 17:09.487
Purdue went to great lengths
to make sure there were

17:09.487 --> 17:12.198
no executives' fingerprints
on anything.

17:12.198 --> 17:13.658
RICK: Like I said,
that's where it gets murky,

17:13.658 --> 17:14.784
but we'll keep digging.

17:14.784 --> 17:16.118
Won't be our entire case,

17:16.118 --> 17:17.995
but it could be great
in terms of proving fraud.

17:17.995 --> 17:19.747
‐ Or at least get a judge
to grant us access

17:19.747 --> 17:21.832
to all Purdue's internal files.

17:21.832 --> 17:24.168
BROWNLEE: Well, you better
find something big, and fast,

17:24.168 --> 17:25.545
because we've got a situation

17:25.545 --> 17:28.172
that might shut
this whole thing down.

